<h2 class="govuk-heading-m">What you'll learn</h2>

<div class="govuk-grid-row">
  <div class="govuk-grid-column-one-half">
    <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">For planning managers</h3>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li>How <a href="https://opendigitalplanning.org/back-office-planning-system-bops" class="govuk-link">BOPS</a> structures the planning application lifecycle</li>
      <li>Dashboard views for case management and workload</li>
      <li>The validation, consultation, assessment, determination workflow</li>
      <li>What applicants see on the public portal</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="govuk-grid-column-one-half">
    <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">For technical staff</h3>
    <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
      <li>ECS Fargate deployment with Aurora PostgreSQL</li>
      <li>Multi-service architecture (web, applicants, worker)</li>
      <li>CloudFront HTTPS termination pattern</li>
      <li>PostGIS spatial data and OS Maps integration</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-m">What's included</h2>

<p class="govuk-body">
  Your deployment comes pre-loaded with:
</p>

<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
  <li><strong>35 planning applications</strong> across householder, prior approval, and lawful development types</li>
  <li><strong>3 user roles</strong> — assessor, reviewer, and administrator</li>
  <li><strong>Varied statuses</strong> — applications at different stages from "not started" to "in assessment"</li>
  <li><strong>10 published applications</strong> visible on the public applicants portal</li>
  <li><strong>Ordnance Survey maps</strong> showing site boundaries</li>
</ul>

